fr.enstb.xmlcode
Class ModelEntity

java.lang.Object
  fr.enstb.xmlcode.ModelEntity

public class ModelEntity
extends java.lang.Object

ModelEntity is internally used in XMLMapping

You never need to used it directly, this class maps <entity> tags in model file.

Author:
Sylvain Guerin
See Also:
XMLMapping

            throws InvalidModelException
Creates a new ModelEntity instance
This constructor should be called for dynamically XMLMapping building purposes.
Use XMLMapping.registerNewModelEntity(ModelEntity) to register this new ModelEntity object in an XMLMapping instance. Use registerNewModelProperty(ModelProperty) to register new ModelPropery objects.

Parameters:
someXMLTags - comma separated strings coding all the values a XML tag could take
Throws:
InvalidModelException - if an error occurs
